window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>The dragon's out of the bag in this diverse, young urban fantasy from an award-winning author!</p> <p>When Jaxon is sent to spend the day with a mean old lady his mother calls Ma, he finds out she's not his grandmother - but she is a witch! She needs his help delivering baby dragons to a magical world where they'll be safe.&nbsp;</p> <p>There are two rules when it comes to the dragons: Don't let them out of the bag, and don't feed them anything sweet. Before he knows it, Jax and his friends Vikram and Kavita have broken both rules!&nbsp;</p> <p>Will Jax get the baby dragons delivered safe and sound? Or will they be lost in Brooklyn forever?</p> <p><b>An NPR Best Book of the Year</b></p> <p><b>A Chicago Public Library Best Book of the Year</b></p> <p><b>A</b><b><i> Kirkus Reviews</i></b><b> Best Book of the Year</b></p>"; 
